The COL mathematical and logic operations between columns uses the "Y"
command to mark the columns to be operated upon and the "=" command to
locate the placement of the answer.  Any valid REXX arithmetic,
comparison, logical or string operation may be used between the columns.
 
Example:
????????????YYYYYYY * YYYYYYYY===========?????????????
                  5          2
                100         50
 
Yields:
                  5          2         10
                100         50       5000
 
Example:
????????????YYYYYYY / YYYYYYYY * 10 ====.=====?????????????
              123.5         22
                100          3
 
Yields:
              123.5         22        56.13636
                100          3       333.33333
 
The columns are operated upon left to right.
The equal signs for the answer placement may be located anywhere.
The decimal in the "=" string is optional and locates the decimal point.
Existing text within the "=" answer column is overlaid.
The columns themselves may include the operators.
 
The columns may contain REXX functions to be evaluated.
 
Mathematical expressions may be formed in three ways.
 
1. The columns, answer and operators may be specified in the
   COL command line:
2. The column and answer may be specified in the
   COL command line with the operators in the text.
3. Named columns with the function entered in the XEDIT command line:
 
