When not using named columns, the text columns marked with "Y" are
extracted, the operators entered in the command line are interleaved into
the text and the resulting text string passed to REXX for interpretation.
The result is then overlaid into the "=" location.
 
When using named columns, the values within the columns are placed into
REXX Variables for evaluation within the expression as entered on the
XEDIT command line.  The answer is then placed in the columns identified
by the string of equal signs.  The first column is named y.1, the second
is named y.2 and so forth.  The contents of the answer column prior to
evaluation is named y.0.  You may also name the columns yourself as:
 
   ????????????YYYYYYa   YYYYYYYb ==========?????????????
   On the XEDIT command line enter ====> y.a / y.b
 
 
NOTES:
If the length of the "=" string exceeds 9, REXX's Numeric Digits setting
is increased to match during this operation.
 
Text is left justified.
